Cordeiro stepped down amid an outcry over the US women’s national soccer team’s pay equity lawsuit. Wilson, a former Executive Vice President at the Wasserman sports agency, joins new President Cindy Parlow Cone as the organisation aims to “grow participation levels and increase our commercial business. I have always admired the federation,” Wilson said in a statement. “There is nothing like harnessing our nation’s support behind our women’s and men’s national teams.” Wilson joins the governing body amid a state of flux for professional sport, with the coronavirus pandemic prompting the likely postponement of the upcoming Olympic Games. --Reuters--